From Steve Dyer Subject Re Frequent nosebleeds In article Robert Allison writes Does anyone know of any method to reduce this frequency My younger brothers each tried a skin transplant thigh to nose lining but their nosebleeds soon I've seen a reference to an herb called Rutin that is supposed to help and I'd like to hear of experiences with it or other Rutin is a bioflavonoid compounds found among other places in the rinds of citrus These have been popular especially in Europe to treat capillary fragility and seemingly in even more extreme cases a few months ago a friend was visiting from Italy and he said that he'd had hemorrhoids but his pharmacist friend sold him some Incredulously I asked to look at them and sure enough these contained rutin as the active I probably destroyed the placebo effect from my skeptical I have no idea how he's doing hemorrhoid wise these The studies which attempted to look at the effect of these compounds in human disease and nutrition were never very well controlled so the reports of positive results with them is mostly This stuff is pretty much non toxic and probably inexpensive so there's little risk of trying it but I wouldn't expect much of a Steve Dyer aka ima harvard rayssd linus spdcc dyer